    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhile doing simple math of the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\n0 + 1\r\n2 + 2\r\n4 + 3\r\n6 + 4\r\n```\r\n\r\nby following instructions of https://vimtricks.com/p/vim-calculator/, exceptly I use also macro to apply things to multiple lines\r\n\r\nwhile using macro I got the following displayed in command \r\n\r\n```\r\n=2 + 2^M4 + 3^M6 +\r\nE488: Trailing characters: ^M4 + 3^M6 +\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\n0 + 1\r\n2 + 2\r\n4 + 3\r\n6 + 4\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. starts at the first line\r\n2. qb start recording\r\n3. v$y copy the content\r\n4. `A = <c-r>= <c-r>\"<cr>`\r\n5. esc\r\n6. q stop recording\r\n7. `<c-v>` and select the following 3 lines\r\n8. @b apply the macro\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nno ^M character in command\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux mint 21.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty 0.11.0 (8dbaa0b)\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\napt-repository",
