            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The OP's reproduction step is different from what is explained in https://vimtricks.com/p/vim-calculator/.\r\n\r\nI think the key sequence intended by OP is\r\n\r\n```\r\nqb\r\n0\r\nv$y\r\nA = <C-r>=<c-r>\"<CR>\r\n<Esc>\r\nq\r\nj\r\n@b\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn step 4 `\"` (i.e. pasting what was yanked int the `<C-R>` expression) is missing.\r\n\r\nBut this is not a valid because @GopherJ is using `v$y` instead of `vww` as explained in the referred doc -- the difference is that `v$y` yanks through the end of line which includes the EOL character (or line feed `^M`). So I think neovim is working as intended.\r\n\r\n@GopherJ  You'll need to do `v$hy` or adjust the visual selection range properly so that it doesn't copy the `^M` character. Without that (e.g. change `v$y` to `v$hy`), the macro works as the you want.\r\n",
